            <biogHist>
                <p>Catherine MacPherson was born to John and Marion n√©e McPhee, her father was a
                    fisherman. At some point before 1861 she married Alexander MacFarlane, but the
                    two are not recorded staying together. The 1861 Census has her living with her
                    younger sister, Anne, who works as a domestic servant, while Catherine is a
                    crofter. Ten years later, is is recorded as staying with her brother, John, with
                    his family. He had been a corporal in the army and was widowed. It was during
                    this period she met Carmichael and sang 'Is Ann A Ghabh Mi Mo Chead' for him.
                    Catherine died nine years, on the 4 January 1880, at Kentangaval suffering from
                    asthma bronchitis. Her brother John signed the death certificate. She was still
                    recorded as married.</p>
